<h3>New</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Multi-language support</strong>: The app is now available in Simplified Chinese, Traditional Chinese, Japanese, and Spanish — in addition to English and Korean.</li>
  <li><strong>Session completion</strong>: Click the circle next to any session to mark it complete. Completed sessions appear dimmed with a strikethrough, and you can hide them with one click to keep your list tidy.</li>
  <li><strong>Multi-selection in Sessions</strong>: ⌘-click or ⇧-click to select multiple sessions, then right-click to pin, mark complete, or delete them all at once.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Improved</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Sessions tab</strong>: The "History" tab is now called "Sessions" across all supported languages.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Fixed</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Markdown in assistant responses now renders immediately when a text block settles, rather than waiting for the full response to complete.</li>
  <li>Built-in slash commands updated to match the latest Claude Code CLI reference.</li>
  <li>Trailing space below the final response paragraph is now correctly reserved, preventing text from touching the bottom edge.</li>
  <li>Session sidecar fields (pin, completion state) are now preserved when the watcher reloads a session from disk.</li>
</ul>
      ]]></description>
